ing</span><hr size=1> A good friend of mine who I've played EQ with for the last 2 years pretty much every day got banned last night for &quot;aiding in the compromising of another's account.&quot;  I am a horrible judge of character but I know beyond a shadow of a doubt that my friend would not &quot;compromise another's account&quot;.<br>
<br>
A relatively mild person from Swords for Hire was banned last month for causing a ruckus or some such when she's shown no inclination to be a &quot;rabble rouser&quot; in the year and a half that I've known her (other than to sign the druid petition).<br>
<br>
I read on other boards of people being banned because of LDing while zoning because some people do that to crash the zone - even though they had no such goal.  There have been a couple other threads from some confused people asking why they were banned.  The conclusion I would make is that while there have always been stories of people mistakenly being banned, there seems to be an increase in this activity in the last couple months...and now it has struck closer to home in the form of my trustworthy friend.  <br>
<br>
